 Paralympic Committee (IPC).\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 395, \"end\": 401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9979998930397209, \"rank\": 0.001658300925423043, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 502, \"end\": 539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 548, \"end\": 588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Paralympic Committee (IPC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All medals\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 291}, {\"ngram\": \"the name\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 318}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 331}, {\"ngram\": \"the discipline\", \"from\": 333, \"to\": 347}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 361}, {\"ngram\": \"the edge\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic medals\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 423}, {\"ngram\": \"English\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 438}, {\"ngram\": \"theParalympicones\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 459}, {\"ngram\": \"the respective official languages\", \"from\": 461, \"to\": 494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On each medal, original iron from the Eiffel Tower has been cut into a hexagon - the shape that has been used as a nickname for France.\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 726, \"entities