lympic gold medals have some gold in them but they are mostly made of silver.\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2196, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic gold medals\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2137}, {\"ngram\": \"some gold\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2152}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2195}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the IOC, gold and silver medals are required to be made of at least 92.5 per cent silver.\", \"from\": 2198, \"to\": 2300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2215, \"end\": 2218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.719582624344257e-23, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold and silver medals\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2242}, {\"ngram\": \"at least 92.5 per cent silver\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2299}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gold plating on the outside layer of the medal must consist of at least six grams of pure gold.\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2401, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The gold\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2310}, {\"ngram\": \"the outside layer\", \"from\": 2322, \"to\": 2339}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2352}, {\"ngram\": \"at least six grams\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2387}, {\"ngram\": \"pure gold\", \"from\": 2391, \"to\": 2400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Medals produced:5,084Diameter:85mmThickness:9.2mmGold medal weight:529gSilver medal weight:525gBronze medal weight:455g Each medal contains 18g of iron from the Eiffel Tower Meanwhile, silver medals are made of pure silver, while bronze medals are 95 per cent copper and five per cent zinc.\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2695, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Medals\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2409}, {\"ngram\": \"medal weight:529